    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-09-08T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-09-08T14:00:00-05:00" n="67"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d67">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">715.1715/575: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cramp</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-09-08T13:00:00-06:00"
                            >September 8, 1937—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 4:34 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>58. I have just learned that the Director of Posts here has agreed not to place
                    the blue sticker on mail for Nicaragua, reciprocating the agreement of the
                    Director of Posts in Nicaragua not to put the Nicaraguan stamp on mail destined
                    here. This was arranged through the good offices of Pan American Airways in both
                    capitals.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cramp</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
